frus:attachment.p:
The young women whom Miss Fletcher and Miss Palmer wish to have go with them
                        are from other islands—Rhoda, Esther, and Edith, from the Mortlock group;
                        Aleta, from the Mokie Island; Myra, Lulu, Mary Jane Smith, and Nancy Oldham,
                        from the Mokil Island; Elsie and Sophie Juniper, from the Marshall group;
                        Nellie and Jael, from Pingalap Island. These girls were allowed to leave the
                        island September 11, 1890. They returned here September 29, 1890.
